      "title": {
        "en": "The Lardarina Staircase",
        "de": "Was Corniglia besonders macht",
        "fr": "Ce qui rend Corniglia spécial",
        "it": "L'Anima Autentica"
      },
      "subtitle": {
        "en": "382 brick steps connect the train station to the village above."
      },
      "content": {
        "en": "Arriving in Corniglia requires effort—the famous Lardarina staircase winds up the cliff from the train station. Each step brings you closer to one of Cinque Terre's best-kept secrets. For those who prefer not to climb, a shuttle bus runs periodically from the station. The climb is rewarded with stunning views and a village that feels genuinely local, where elderly residents still tend rooftop gardens and laundry hangs from windows."
      }
    },
