        "en": "Local Specialty"
      },
      "title": {
        "en": "Alberto's Legendary Gelato"
      },
      "subtitle": {
        "en": "A pilgrimage destination for gelato lovers"
      },
      "content": {
        "en": "Gelateria Alberto has achieved cult status among Cinque Terre visitors. Located on the main street, this tiny shop produces some of Italy's most innovative flavors using hyper-local ingredients. The basil gelato uses herbs from nearby gardens, the honey comes from hillside beehives, and the Sciacchetrà flavor incorporates the region's famous dessert wine. In summer, the queue stretches down the street—but it's worth every minute of waiting."
      },
      "testimonial": {
        "quote": {
          "en": "I've eaten gelato all over Italy, and Alberto's is genuinely exceptional. The basil-honey combination is unlike anything else. We climbed those 382 steps just for this."
        },
